{"TROPAEOLIN":[{"def":"A name given to any one of a series of orange-red dyestuffs produced artificially from certain complex sulphonic acid derivatives of azo and diazo hydrocarbons of the aromatic series; -- so called because of the general resemblance to the shades of nasturtium (Tropæolum).","pos":""}],"TROPE":[{"def":"In his frequent, long, and tedious speeches, it has been said that a trope never passed his lips.","pos":""}],"TROPEINE":[{"def":"Any one of a series of artificial ethereal salts derived from the alkaloidal base tropine.","pos":""}],"TROPHI":[{"def":"The mouth parts of an insect, collectively, including the labrum, labium, maxillæ, mandibles, and lingua, with their appendages.","pos":""}],"TROPHIC":[{"def":"Of or connected with nutrition; nitritional; nourishing; as, the so-called trophic nerves, which have a direct influence on nutrition.","pos":""}],"TROPHIED":[{"def":"Adorned with trophies.","pos":""}],"TROPHONIAN":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to Trophonius, his architecture, or his cave and oracle.","pos":""}],"TROPHOSOME":[{"def":"The nutritive zooids of a hydroid, collectively, as distinguished from the gonosome, or reproductive zooids.","pos":""}],"TROPHY":[{"def":"A sign or memorial of a victory raised on the field of battle, or, in case of a naval victory, on the nearest land.","pos":""}],"TROPIC":[{"def":"Of, pertaining to, or designating, an acid obtained from atropine and certain other alkaloids, as a white crystalline substance slightly soluble in water.","pos":""}],"TROPICAL":[{"def":"Rhetorically changed from its exact original sense; being of the nature of a trope; figurative; metaphorical.","pos":""}],"TROPICALLY":[{"def":"In a tropical manner; figuratively; metaphorically.","pos":""}],"TROPIDINE":[{"def":"An alkaloid, C8H13N, obtained by the chemical dehydration of tropine, as an oily liquid having a coninelike odor.","pos":""}],"TROPILIDENE":[{"def":"A liquid hydrocarbon obtained by the dry distillation of tropine with quicklime.","pos":""}],"TROPINE":[{"def":"A white crystalline alkaloid, C8H15NO, produced by decomposing atropine.","pos":""}],"TROPISM":[{"def":"Modification of the direction of growth.","pos":""}],"TROPIST":[{"def":"One who deals in tropes; specifically, one who avoids the literal sense of the language of Scripture by explaining it as mere tropes and figures of speech.","pos":""},{"def":"Characterized by tropes; varied by tropes; tropical.","pos":""}],"TROPOLOGIZE":[{"def":"To use in a tropological sense, as a word; to make a trope of.","pos":""}],"TROPOLOGY":[{"def":"A rhetorical mode of speech, including tropes, or changes from the original import of the word.","pos":""}],"TROPPO":[{"def":"Too much; as, allegro ma non troppo, brisk but not too much so.","pos":""}]}